HEADWORD: Perpendicle
<hw>Per*pen"di*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>perpendiculum</ets>; <ets>per</ets> + <ets>pendere</ets> to hang:
cf. F. <ets>perpendicule</ets>.]</ety> <def>Something hanging straight
down; a plumb line.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perpendicular</ent>⟦br⟧
